04:51.037 --> 04:53.405
(Heavy breathing)

04:54.740 --> 04:56.708
(Whimpering)

04:56.742 --> 04:58.677
(Grunting)

04:58.711 --> 04:59.778
Malcolm.

04:59.812 --> 05:01.046
Where is he?

05:01.080 --> 05:02.847
I don't know.

05:02.882 --> 05:04.816
You have one second.

05:04.850 --> 05:06.885
He... he tried to recruit me.

05:06.919 --> 05:08.954
I hid instead.

05:08.988 --> 05:11.890
I know better than to
go against The Pack.

05:11.924 --> 05:13.391
Let him talk.

05:13.425 --> 05:15.126
What if I let him die instead?

05:15.160 --> 05:17.361
Oh, no, no, there's a meet-up...

05:17.396 --> 05:19.830
for any Mutt that wants to join Malcolm.

05:19.864 --> 05:21.865
4:30 at the docks.

05:21.900 --> 05:24.001
How do you know that?

05:24.035 --> 05:25.769
One of Malcolm's lackeys called me,

05:25.804 --> 05:27.671
um... Nate...

05:27.706 --> 05:28.839
Nathan?

05:28.873 --> 05:30.407
Ferret-faced guy.

05:30.441 --> 05:32.209
He told me there'd be a meet-up

05:32.243 --> 05:34.612
for anyone who wanted to join Malcolm.

05:34.646 --> 05:36.814
They'll know where Malcolm is.

05:36.848 --> 05:39.382
I don't want any part of their crap.

05:39.417 --> 05:41.685
I heard what they did to your boyfriend.

05:41.720 --> 05:44.622
(Grunting, panting)

05:44.656 --> 05:47.157
Nobody deserves to die like that.

05:47.191 --> 05:49.726
(Shaky breaths)

05:49.760 --> 05:52.295
(Grunting)

05:56.534 --> 05:58.935
Jeremy: I understand the
Alpha council's concern,

05:58.969 --> 06:02.872
but we cannot change what has happened.

06:02.906 --> 06:05.608
(Russian accent) It is the actions
of your Pack in the last few months

06:05.643 --> 06:07.810
that is the problem, Danvers.

06:07.845 --> 06:09.612
That this Mutt uprising could happen

06:09.647 --> 06:12.682
on your territory in the first place

06:12.716 --> 06:14.017
is not without issue.

06:14.051 --> 06:16.019
(Speaking in Korean)

06:17.955 --> 06:19.855
I was not complacent with them,

06:19.889 --> 06:21.757
I made an example out of them.

06:21.791 --> 06:24.527
I'm not interested in wallowing
over whys and what-ifs.

06:24.561 --> 06:27.463
Perhaps you want us
to do what you cannot.

06:27.497 --> 06:29.064
Find your father and kill him.

06:29.098 --> 06:31.867
My Pack will find and kill
Malcolm for what he's done:

06:31.901 --> 06:33.769
The Mutt uprising,

06:33.803 --> 06:37.605
the death of two of my Pack
and seven innocent humans.

06:37.640 --> 06:40.575
And he has taken something
of great importance to us.

06:40.609 --> 06:42.010
(Scoffing)

06:42.045 --> 06:46.782
You see, our problem is
not Malcolm Danvers.

06:46.816 --> 06:50.118
(Speaking in Russian)
You know this Russian proverb?

06:50.153 --> 06:52.920
"The fish rots from the head."

06:52.954 --> 06:55.557
This is a Spanish proverb.

06:55.591 --> 06:58.259
It is fact.

06:58.294 --> 07:02.497
Our Packs are a reflection
of our leadership.

07:02.531 --> 07:05.667
And your leadership is weak.

07:05.701 --> 07:07.868
You want to make an example of Malcolm?

07:07.903 --> 07:11.072
We need to make an example of you.

07:11.106 --> 07:14.809
An Alpha cannot show
his throat like this.

07:18.546 --> 07:20.981
Is not personal, is politics.

07:23.318 --> 07:25.852
There's nothing more
personal than politics.

07:25.886 --> 07:28.922
You have one week to deliver
us proof of Malcolm's death.

07:28.956 --> 07:30.790
And if I don't?

07:30.825 --> 07:32.559
We'll find him for you

07:32.594 --> 07:34.561
and take control of
your Pack in the process.

07:38.032 --> 07:39.666
Very well.

07:39.701 --> 07:44.170
While my Pack searches for Malcolm here,
why don't you spend the week in Montana.

07:44.205 --> 07:45.939
It's spectacular.

07:45.973 --> 07:48.742
I will stay and assist in
the search for Malcolm.

07:48.776 --> 07:49.876
That won't be necessary.

07:49.910 --> 07:51.677
I insist.

07:51.712 --> 07:53.880
It will be a chance for us
to get to know each other,

07:53.914 --> 07:55.181
as Alphas.

07:55.216 --> 07:57.984
I welcome your stay.

07:58.018 --> 08:00.519
And when you gentlemen return,

08:00.554 --> 08:03.522
Malcolm's head will be on a stake.

08:03.557 --> 08:05.958
My Pack is diligently
searching for him now.

08:05.992 --> 08:09.073
( ♪ )

08:22.842 --> 08:25.944
Aren't we going inside?

08:25.979 --> 08:27.379
Of course, I just have a little...

08:27.413 --> 08:29.447
