(Panting)

11:00.494 --> 11:04.031
(Heavy panting)

11:04.065 --> 11:07.603
( ♪ )

11:13.141 --> 11:16.843
Huh... so Jakob's dead.

11:16.877 --> 11:18.945
What was he doing throwing
in with Malcolm Danvers

11:18.979 --> 11:20.279
and attacking Stonehaven?

11:20.314 --> 11:22.348
You deserve to know.

11:22.382 --> 11:24.751
Elena speaks very highly of you.

11:24.785 --> 11:26.218
She says you play by the rules.

11:26.253 --> 11:28.955
You didn't come here to
blow sunshine up my ass.

11:28.989 --> 11:31.591
Or to tell me my son died.

11:31.625 --> 11:33.159
Listen, I need to know
what Jakob was up to

11:33.193 --> 11:35.094
before the attack on Stonehaven.

11:35.128 --> 11:37.648
Did he ever mention where Malcolm
may have based his operations?

11:40.000 --> 11:43.169
See, Malcolm has something of mine,

11:43.203 --> 11:44.303
I need to go find it, get it back.

11:44.338 --> 11:45.771
This ain't my problem.

11:45.805 --> 11:48.240
Listen, it's my girlfriend.

11:48.275 --> 11:49.775
That's who Malcolm has.

11:49.809 --> 11:52.410
She's pregnant with my son.

11:55.014 --> 11:57.215
You had a son,

11:57.249 --> 11:59.751
so surely you understand.

11:59.786 --> 12:02.253
I need to find her, she's my life.

12:05.825 --> 12:07.325
I got a couple of phone calls

12:07.360 --> 12:09.127
from Jakob a week ago.

12:09.161 --> 12:11.529
He owed money to some meth
dealer from Rochester,

12:11.563 --> 12:13.865
wanted me to pay him off
next time I was through.

12:13.899 --> 12:15.967
Okay, Rochester.

12:16.002 --> 12:17.835
You have the number of that dealer?

12:22.274 --> 12:24.876
Meet-up's in 30.

12:24.910 --> 12:26.944
Eventually you're
going to have to exhale.

12:28.947 --> 12:30.280
I'm fine.

12:30.315 --> 12:31.516
Can we finish this?

12:31.550 --> 12:33.417
You're not fine.

12:33.451 --> 12:36.453
It's only been three days since...

12:36.488 --> 12:38.355
You can't ignore your grief.

12:40.825 --> 12:43.860
You have to deal with Philip's death.

12:43.895 --> 12:45.396
Jorge dealt with it.

12:48.066 --> 12:50.501
Jorge dealt with covering it up.

12:50.535 --> 12:52.436
And that's done.

12:52.470 --> 12:55.506
But Phillip's sister has
been texting me ever since.

12:55.540 --> 12:56.973
As far as his family knows,

12:57.008 --> 12:58.608
his car crashed on the way to the airport

12:58.643 --> 13:00.510
and they assume I have
nothing to do with it.

13:00.545 --> 13:03.479
You didn't.

13:03.514 --> 13:04.915
You know that's not true.

13:07.484 --> 13:09.019
We're wasting time, let's go.

13:10.387 --> 13:12.488
Elena...

13:12.523 --> 13:14.424
I admire your sense of calm.

13:14.458 --> 13:16.926
If I had a week to find my mortal enemy,

13:16.960 --> 13:20.196
I assure you, I wouldn't
be entertaining guests.

13:20.230 --> 13:24.833
Well... I admire your
generosity, to help.

13:24.868 --> 13:27.570
Most Alphas would've
opted to see me fail,

13:27.604 --> 13:31.073
then staked a claim to my
territory in North America.

13:34.310 --> 13:37.580
The way he sat there in your chair.

13:37.614 --> 13:41.584
Roman Navikev never turns down
a chance to show disrespect.

13:41.618 --> 13:44.352
No.

13:44.387 --> 13:45.954
Not like your father.

13:45.988 --> 13:48.156
There was an Alpha who
ruled with his heart,

13:48.191 --> 13:49.291
not his fist.

13:57.266 --> 13:59.834
What will you do if you
don't find Malcolm?

13:59.868 --> 14:02.604
He could slip away
with the pregnant woman.

14:06.609 --> 14:08.509
He could.

14:08.543 --> 14:10.478
He hasn't had any money to speak of

14:10.512 --> 14:12.914
since I closed his
account a few years ago,

14:12.948 --> 14:14.882
yet he managed an uprising.

14:14.917 --> 14:16.718
You think someone is backing him?

14:18.686 --> 14:22.556
Treachery is easier to
hide from across an ocean.

14:22.591 --> 14:23.890
And it does seem to be someone

14:23.925 --> 14:25.493
who is hungry for North America.

14:27.629 --> 14:30.197
Navikev.

14:30.232 --> 14:31.432
You are clever.

14:31.466 --> 14:33.434
He underestimated you.

14:33.468 --> 14:35.401
You will need proof.

14:35.436 --> 14:37.104
Follow the money.

14:37.138 --> 14:39.906
If I find that Roman was involved,

14:39.941 --> 14:44.244
do I have your support in killing him?

14:44.278 --> 14:46.246
My support?

14:46.280 --> 14:47.614
I swear to you

14:47.649 --> 14:49.482
on the blood of my infant son

14:49.517 --> 14:52.418
that I will personally
place his head on a stake

14:52.453 --> 14:54.387
beside Malcolm's.

14:54.421 --> 14:57.757
Wait at your hotel for word.

14:57.791 --> 15:01.561
We will finish this... together.

15:03.497 --> 15:04.797
Hm.

15:06.500 --> 15:07.800
Not much of a meet-up.

15:10.503 --> 15:12.138
Elena: One Mutt is all we need.

15:17.914 --> 15:19.554
Elena: We're going to play a little game.

15:19.579 --> 15:21.681
I ask, you answer.

15:23.650 --> 15:25.350
Both: (Grunting)

15:25.385 --> 15:27.986
(Metal banging)
Ughh!

15:28.020 --> 15:31.290
Malcolm Danvers. Where is he?

15:31.324 --> 15:33.492
You're going to let a girl
do your fighting for you?

15:34.627 --> 15:35.727
(Bang)
Ohhhh...

15:35.761 --> 15:37.696
You got another stupid question?

15:37.730 --> 15:39.931
Elena: Malcolm. Spit it out.

15:39.965 --> 15:42.834
I don't know. You know as much as I do.

15:44.203 --> 15:47.305
I know your contact is Nate Parker.

15:47.339 --> 15:49.580
I've been calling him, you
know, he's just not answering.

15:50.676 --> 15:53.044
(Bone cracking)
(Yelling)

15:53.079 --> 15:54.612
I also know you're meeting Mutts

15:54.646 --> 15:56.981
and taking them to Malcolm.

15:57.016 --> 15:58.249
Looks like no one's interested

15:58.283 --> 16:00.251
in joining your failed uprising.

16:00.285 --> 16:02.019
So tell us where he is

16:02.053 --> 16:03.721
and we'll put an end to this.

16:03.755 --> 16:06.090
If I talk, Malcolm kills me.

16:08.260 --> 16:10.528
- Ugh!
- Tell me what you know

16:10.562 --> 16:11.629
and I'll kill him.

16:11.663 --> 16:14.164
You'll never get to him.

16:14.199 --> 16:16.767
(Yelling, coughing)

16:16.801 --> 16:19.703
I was the one that met your
boyfriend at the airport.

16:19.738 --> 16:21.705
(Groaning)

16:21.740 --> 16:24.641
That was you?

16:24.675 --> 16:26.744
I thought it was Malcolm.

16:26.778 --> 16:28.212
Flight to France.

16:28.246 --> 16:29.579
He didn't make it on.

16:29.614 --> 16:31.248
It's 'cause I got to him first.

16:33.751 --> 16:36.018
Go on. Tell me what happened!

16:36.053 --> 16:38.421
Elena, don't, he's
goading you to kill him.

16:38.456 --> 16:39.723
He was scared.

16:39.757 --> 16:41.524
He was begging for his life.

16:41.559 --> 16:43.526
I took him to the warehouse.

16:43.561 --> 16:45.629
I never decapitated someone before.

16:45.663 --> 16:47.029
Elena.

16:47.064 --> 16:49.331
Shh-h-h... she'll do a much better job

16:49.366 --> 16:51.134
than Malcolm ever would.

16:51.168 --> 16:53.469
Tell me more.

16:53.503 --> 16:54.837
It wasn't easy.

16:54.872 --> 16:57.606
There was all this bone and cartilage.

16:57.641 --> 16:59.275
Have you ever heard someone scream

16:59.309 --> 17:01.410
through gurgling blood?

17:01.444 --> 17:02.711
(Yelling)

17:04.146 --> 17:06.114
(Grunt of effort)
(Screaming)

17:08.417 --> 17:10.252
I have now.

17:10.287 --> 17:11.587
Dammit, Elena, he could've
had more information.

17:11.621 --> 17:13.289
Maybe we needed him.

17:14.523 --> 17:15.691
Ughh!

17:15.724 --> 17:17.459
We don't need him.

17:19.429 --> 17:22.512
( ♪ )

17:37.546 --> 17:38.613
Had to be done.

17:38.647 --> 17:40.615
Fine, yes.

17:40.649 --> 17:43.083
But you should leave
the dirty work to me.

17:43.118 --> 17:44.819
Just because you don't need the ghosts.

17:44.853 --> 17:46.487
You already have enough.

17:46.522 --> 17:47.622
And you don't?

17:51.794 --> 17:55.462
We're here for the one true
cursed, Malcolm Danvers.

17:55.496 --> 17:57.298
Deliver him or die.

18:02.617 --> 18:03.683
For the undoing,

18:03.718 --> 18:05.919
the destroyer comes.

18:05.953 --> 18:08.521
(Fighting grunts)

18:08.555 --> 18:11.669
