19:04.543 --> 19:05.543
Who the hell are they?

19:05.577 --> 19:07.645
No IDs.

19:07.680 --> 19:09.781
Hey, come take a look at this.

19:14.619 --> 19:15.853
They all have it.

19:15.888 --> 19:17.889
Stupid hipsters.

19:17.923 --> 19:19.490
The way they came at us,

19:19.524 --> 19:21.858
it's like they don't feel pain.

19:21.893 --> 19:22.959
And if they're after Malcolm,

19:22.994 --> 19:25.095
what's he gotten himself into?

19:28.066 --> 19:31.146
( ♪ )

19:48.385 --> 19:49.786
(Phone ringing)

19:53.924 --> 19:55.325
Siobhan Devitt.

19:55.359 --> 19:56.759
Joey: (On phone) <i>This is agent Franks</i>

19:56.793 --> 19:58.894
<i>from the Buffalo branch</i>
<i>office of the FBI.</i>

19:58.929 --> 20:01.431
<i>Listen, we've hit a dead end on a case.</i>

20:01.465 --> 20:03.099
Would you be a sweetheart
and pull up an account

20:03.133 --> 20:05.067
to see if there's any activity?

20:05.102 --> 20:07.337
Siobhan: (On phone) <i>That
goes against bank policy.</i>

20:07.371 --> 20:09.404
I know. Just look in the Philippines,

20:09.439 --> 20:11.006
see if there's been any charges.

20:11.041 --> 20:14.409
This guy is, um... sick.

20:15.846 --> 20:17.679
Ten-year-old girl sick.

20:20.416 --> 20:21.717
What's his name?

20:21.752 --> 20:23.152
James Williams.

20:23.186 --> 20:25.621
You can check a shell
company: Viojandi Vodka.

20:25.655 --> 20:28.156
<i>V-I-O-J-A-N-D-I.</i>

20:33.429 --> 20:34.529
(Camera click)

20:37.400 --> 20:39.167
<i>Nothing in the Philippines, sir.</i>

20:39.201 --> 20:40.535
Oh, that's the best news
I've heard all day.

20:40.570 --> 20:41.803
- Thank you.
- We got it.

20:41.837 --> 20:43.638
Malcolm's account?

20:43.672 --> 20:45.974
Nick: (On phone) <i>Under the
alias James Williams.</i>

20:46.008 --> 20:47.976
<i>It looks like a real</i>
<i>travelling road show.</i>

20:48.010 --> 20:49.377
<i>There's withdrawals in...</i>

20:49.411 --> 20:53.782
Des Moines, Vegas, Toronto.

20:53.816 --> 20:56.117
<i>Before; nothing since</i>
<i>the attack on Stonehaven.</i>

20:56.152 --> 20:58.552
But... 27 days ago,

20:58.587 --> 21:01.422
money went out of the
account to Rochester Power.

21:01.456 --> 21:03.957
Malcolm is making utility payments.

21:03.992 --> 21:05.626
That could be his base.

21:05.661 --> 21:07.528
- I'll get on it.
Jeremy: (On phone) <i>- Hold on.</i>

21:07.562 --> 21:09.430
<i>I'll conference in Clay and Elena.</i>

21:11.700 --> 21:14.067
- Hey, what's up?
Jeremy: <i>- We have a lead on Malcolm.</i>

21:14.102 --> 21:15.535
<i>You have to get yourself to Rochester.</i>

21:15.569 --> 21:16.804
We're over an hour away.

21:16.838 --> 21:17.971
Has anyone heard from Logan?

21:18.006 --> 21:19.807
He's still off the grid.

21:19.841 --> 21:22.542
We just got jumped at a Mutt meet-up...
by humans.

21:22.576 --> 21:25.012
They're after Malcolm for some reason.
<i>Malcolm?</i>

21:25.046 --> 21:27.514
We have to get to him first.

21:27.548 --> 21:29.668
The other Alphas have given
us a deadline to find him.

21:29.684 --> 21:30.983
And if we don't?

21:32.553 --> 21:33.920
That's not an option.

21:35.656 --> 21:36.790
We're on our way.

21:41.629 --> 21:43.930
Nick: <i>You didn't really
answer Elena's question.</i>

21:43.964 --> 21:45.765
What happens if we don't find Malcolm?

21:47.634 --> 21:49.635
Then I have to step down,

21:49.669 --> 21:50.903
give up my Pack

21:50.938 --> 21:52.538
<i>and my territory.</i>

21:54.842 --> 21:57.543
Where's the money coming from?

21:57.577 --> 22:01.480
Um, it's a wire transfer...

22:01.514 --> 22:03.649
foreign account. <i>Which country?</i>

22:05.952 --> 22:07.919
Russia.

22:07.954 --> 22:10.689
(Cynical chuckling)

22:10.724 --> 22:12.391
Nick,

22:12.425 --> 22:14.226
<i>I need you to come back to Stonehaven.</i>

22:15.662 --> 22:17.929
We have some business
with the Spanish Alpha.

22:17.964 --> 22:19.931
And Joey?

22:19.966 --> 22:21.233
<i>He's free to go.</i>

22:23.502 --> 22:25.971
You are off the clock, my friend.

22:33.980 --> 22:35.881
You find him.

22:35.915 --> 22:37.081
You find Malcolm

22:37.115 --> 22:39.884
and you kill him.

22:39.918 --> 22:41.285
For our fathers.

22:44.956 --> 22:46.657
Logan: You find Rachel?

22:46.692 --> 22:48.058
Nick: <i>No, and I shouldn't be calling you</i>

22:48.093 --> 22:49.994
<i>without Jeremy knowing,</i>

22:50.028 --> 22:51.863
<i>but we've got a possible</i>
<i>lead on Malcolm.</i>

22:51.897 --> 22:54.098
Where? Look, there's no guarantee

22:54.132 --> 22:55.665
that Malcolm has Rachel, okay?

22:55.700 --> 22:57.601
What are you talking about?
Of course he does.

22:57.635 --> 22:59.203
He was there at Stonehaven
right when she went missing.

22:59.237 --> 23:00.871
Nick: <i>Look, I hear you, I'm just saying</i>

23:00.906 --> 23:02.206
there's no guarantee
that she'll be there.

23:02.240 --> 23:04.674
Just... just where? Come on!

23:04.709 --> 23:08.678
Rochester. 63 Access Road 5.

23:08.713 --> 23:11.247
<i>If you get there first,</i>
<i>you wait for Clay and Elena.</i>

23:11.282 --> 23:14.550
<i>Are you close?</i>
I'm nowhere near Rochester.

23:14.584 --> 23:16.018
Clay and Elena will be there in an hour.

23:16.052 --> 23:17.613
If anything changes, I'll let you know.

23:19.122 --> 23:21.791
How far is Access Road 5?

23:21.825 --> 23:24.527
(Shouting) - How far?
- I don't know, 40 minutes?

23:39.175 --> 23:41.509
You're not eating?

23:41.544 --> 23:43.178
I've learned my lesson.

23:43.212 --> 23:44.546
But, the baby.

23:46.916 --> 23:48.983
You think the sedatives and this slop

23:49.017 --> 23:50.318
are good for him?

23:50.352 --> 23:51.986
Oh, I think they're good for you.

23:53.989 --> 23:55.156
(Shouting) She won't eat.

23:59.194 --> 24:01.496
We've got a problem.

24:01.530 --> 24:03.164
Nate is not returning my calls.

24:03.198 --> 24:05.967
Neither is the other Mutt
that we sent for the meet-up.

24:06.001 --> 24:07.568
If the Pack can get to them,

24:07.602 --> 24:09.036
they can get to us.

24:11.006 --> 24:12.739
S... so we move?

24:13.976 --> 24:16.210
No. We prepare.

24:17.645 --> 24:18.745
(Shaky breath)

24:20.949 --> 24:22.749
Well, go ahead, you might want to sleep

24:22.784 --> 24:24.384
through the battle that's coming.

24:28.890 --> 24:29.957
Go see what that is.

24:34.228 --> 24:35.895
(Crow squawking)

24:46.273 --> 24:48.141
Man: Oh man.

24:48.175 --> 24:49.942
A bird in the house means something bad.

24:49.977 --> 24:52.077
Dead bird means something real bad.

24:58.051 --> 24:59.418
Or real good.

25:01.889 --> 25:05.491
(Ominous music)

25:09.029 --> 25:10.795
(Mixed whispers) What is happening?

25:10.830 --> 25:13.832
(Electricity crackles; eerie
sounds stop, crickets chirp)

25:13.866 --> 25:15.167
Ahhh!

25:18.281 --> 25:21.590
( ♪ )

25:28.625 --> 25:29.691
Rachel?

25:33.596 --> 25:36.765
(Ominous music)

25:36.799 --> 25:39.534
(Thud)
(Gasp)

25:48.778 --> 25:51.745
(Slow thuds continue)

25:58.654 --> 26:02.230
( ♪ )

26:10.264 --> 26:11.565
(Thud)

26:13.001 --> 26:15.135
Hey, hey, look at me.

26:15.170 --> 26:16.804
Where is she? (Heavy breathing)

26:16.838 --> 26:19.206
Where's Rachel?

26:19.240 --> 26:21.575
It's all coming to an end.

26:21.609 --> 26:22.843
We're all going to die.

26:22.877 --> 26:24.010
No! Who took her?

26:24.044 --> 26:26.145
(Car door closing)

26:26.180 --> 26:28.548
No, no, no, no, no, no!

26:28.583 --> 26:29.816
I don't want to go with them.

26:29.850 --> 26:30.950
Don't make me go with them.

26:30.984 --> 26:32.252
I can't take it.

26:32.286 --> 26:33.553
No, no, no! Where is she?

26:33.588 --> 26:35.188
Where did Malcolm take her?

26:40.227 --> 26:42.695
(Door opens, closes)

26:48.035 --> 26:49.602
What the hell happened here?

26:51.038 --> 26:53.572
Logan: I have no idea.

26:53.607 --> 26:54.841
I followed Malcolm's trail

26:54.875 --> 26:57.042
into the field out back, but...

26:57.076 --> 26:58.844
it was too faint.

26:58.878 --> 26:59.978
What about Rachel?

27:06.085 --> 27:08.854
Wait a minute. Wait.

27:08.888 --> 27:10.021
This is Rachel's.

27:10.056 --> 27:11.990
She was here.

27:12.024 --> 27:13.225
They could be out there.

27:13.259 --> 27:14.893
- We've got to go.
- No, hang on.

27:16.695 --> 27:17.863
Have you slept?

27:17.897 --> 27:19.697
Look at you, you're a wreck.

27:19.732 --> 27:21.666
Look at me?

27:21.700 --> 27:23.034
Look at the blood.

27:23.069 --> 27:24.169
Look at the bodies.

27:24.203 --> 27:25.603
This guy was delusional.

27:25.638 --> 27:27.773
Whatever Malcolm did to
him, to these Mutts,

27:27.807 --> 27:29.674
he has Rachel, we can't stop now!

27:29.708 --> 27:32.677
And go where?

27:32.711 --> 27:35.313
Anywhere but here.

27:35.347 --> 27:36.648
Come on.

27:46.124 --> 27:47.324
(Camera click)

27:47.358 --> 27:51.728
(Eerie music)

27:51.763 --> 27:52.830
(Grunting)

28:00.272 --> 28:01.738
Woman: Top you up?

28:11.115 --> 28:12.349
Keep the change.

28:12.383 --> 28:13.717
Thank you.

28:15.019 --> 28:16.486
Mighty kind.

28:18.690 --> 28:20.023
Nothing more life affirming

28:20.057 --> 28:21.724
than when all your plans and preparation

28:21.758 --> 28:23.126
go out the window.

28:23.160 --> 28:25.528
Man plans, God laughs.

28:28.165 --> 28:29.332
If that's the case,

28:29.366 --> 28:31.935
God's doubled over right now.

28:31.969 --> 28:33.069
Where you headed?

28:36.306 --> 28:38.307
How do you know I'm headed anywhere?

28:38.342 --> 28:40.008
I'm from nowhere,

28:40.043 --> 28:42.712
and even I wouldn't say
this place is somewhere.

28:46.516 --> 28:50.285
I'm headed south, Mississippi Way.

28:50.320 --> 28:52.087
I can take you as far as Cincinnati.

28:52.121 --> 28:53.155
If you're in need for a drive.

28:53.189 --> 28:56.725
(Paper rustling)

28:56.759 --> 28:58.526
That's mighty kind too.

28:58.561 --> 29:02.064
(Ominous music)

29:02.098 --> 29:04.733
(Bees buzzing)

29:12.207 --> 29:14.942
Should we stop him?

29:14.977 --> 29:17.178
We're too exposed here.

29:17.212 --> 29:18.747
We follow him.

29:26.321 --> 29:28.722
Did you hear anything
from Clay and Elena?

29:28.757 --> 29:30.457
It was carnage at the house.

29:30.492 --> 29:32.826
No sign of Malcolm or Rachel.

29:32.861 --> 29:35.162
This is no time to be
delicate with Alpha politics.

29:35.197 --> 29:37.331
They've given you a deadline, Jeremy.

29:37.366 --> 29:39.166
We'll give them Malcolm.
This is the way.

29:39.201 --> 29:40.434
Rodrigo Sanchez,

29:40.468 --> 29:43.704
may I present Nick Sorentino.

29:43.738 --> 29:46.106
Nick was in New York on business.

29:46.140 --> 29:48.375
He was tracking down Malcolm's accounts.

29:48.410 --> 29:49.777
Or rather the accounts

29:49.811 --> 29:51.278
of the alias that Malcolm was using,

29:51.312 --> 29:53.146
- James Williams.
- Hmm.

29:53.180 --> 29:56.383
You tell Rodrigo what you found, Nick.

29:56.418 --> 29:57.885
Well, we tracked the money.

29:57.919 --> 29:59.520
And we found out that
Malcolm was financed

29:59.553 --> 30:02.755
by a bank account that
originated in Russia.

30:02.790 --> 30:04.557
You have the proof you needed.

30:04.591 --> 30:06.793
Roman Navikev is backing Malcolm.

30:06.827 --> 30:09.262
He is the fish that is rotting
from head to tail.

30:09.297 --> 30:10.830
Jeremy: Yes.

30:10.864 --> 30:13.233
That was very convenient.

30:13.267 --> 30:17.570
Only, I know that Roman has
never met with my father.

30:17.604 --> 30:20.339
And you say that you haven't either.

30:20.373 --> 30:24.142
Yet you know the woman
he took was pregnant.

30:24.176 --> 30:26.411
I was very careful never
to reveal that fact.

30:28.414 --> 30:29.948
What do you smell, Nick?

30:29.982 --> 30:33.251
(Deep inhalation)

30:33.285 --> 30:35.086
Fear.

30:35.120 --> 30:37.355
That's why werewolves can
never play poker together.

30:37.389 --> 30:39.958
There are two ways
to be a traitor, Rodrigo.

30:41.994 --> 30:44.829
You can be a man and do it in the open,

30:44.863 --> 30:46.597
or you can be a weasel.

30:48.400 --> 30:50.868
And you, my friend...

30:50.902 --> 30:52.003
are a weasel.

30:54.149 --> 30:56.149
You financed Malcolm through
a Russian bank account

30:56.174 --> 30:57.975
so that I would blame
Roman if I went looking.

30:57.976 --> 31:02.145
Jeremy, this is a mistake. No!

31:02.180 --> 31:04.247
Because you wanted Malcolm
running things over here.

31:04.282 --> 31:05.449
If you want to live,

31:05.484 --> 31:06.884
you start talking right now.

31:06.918 --> 31:08.953
Where is Malcolm?

31:08.987 --> 31:10.053
Where is he?

31:10.088 --> 31:11.989
Malcolm called me an hour ago.

31:12.023 --> 31:15.392
He asked me to... to wire
$200,000 to Baton Rouge.

31:15.426 --> 31:17.995
Baton Rouge. Clay might know where he is.

31:18.029 --> 31:20.563
Rodrigo: Th-that's all I know, I swear!

31:20.598 --> 31:23.800
(Choking)
(Softly) Rodrigo,

31:23.834 --> 31:25.402
it would be a shame if I found out

31:25.436 --> 31:28.004
that you knew more
and you didn't tell us.

31:28.038 --> 31:30.840
Especially about the pregnant girl.

31:30.875 --> 31:34.143
Malcolm is flying to
Bangkok tomorrow night.

31:34.177 --> 31:36.479
What about the girl? That's
all I know about her,

31:36.514 --> 31:38.815
except that Malcolm had her.

31:38.849 --> 31:40.717
If he gets on that
flight, we've lost him.

31:42.052 --> 31:44.086
I could kill you right now, Rodrigo.

31:44.121 --> 31:45.354
Yeah?

31:45.389 --> 31:47.423
(Choking, straining)

31:47.457 --> 31:49.325
(Gasping) But I'm going
to give you a chance

31:49.359 --> 31:51.460
to do the right thing.

31:51.495 --> 31:53.595
Every Pack would stand against you

31:53.630 --> 31:56.032
if they found out that
you tried to frame Roman

31:56.066 --> 31:58.434
and steal my territory in North America.

32:00.537 --> 32:02.237
What would you have me do?

32:02.271 --> 32:05.674
You just stand by until I contact you.

32:05.708 --> 32:08.544
Say you have some business in New York.

32:08.578 --> 32:10.445
And trust me,

32:10.479 --> 32:13.481
if Roman ever found out
what you had done,

32:13.516 --> 32:17.118
he wouldn't kill your infant son,

32:17.153 --> 32:18.920
he would skin him alive.

32:22.791 --> 32:26.428
Younger woman:
Where did the werewolf go?

32:31.133 --> 32:33.568
<i>Sequere lupus.</i>

32:35.571 --> 32:37.705
Woman: Left it is, then.

32:49.284 --> 32:51.918
Malcolm: Any chance
this truck goes faster?

32:51.953 --> 32:54.354
It might, but I don't.

32:54.389 --> 32:56.923
I like a steady pace.

32:56.958 --> 32:59.893
8 hours, 15 minutes each way

32:59.927 --> 33:03.730
from our farm to my
sister-in-law's place.

33:03.764 --> 33:06.332
You've got it down to a fine science.

33:06.366 --> 33:09.069
Been doing this drive a lot.

33:09.103 --> 33:11.871
My sister-in-law, she
ain't doing too well.

33:11.906 --> 33:15.374
My wife goes up there, stays with her.

33:15.409 --> 33:18.144
Cancer of the pancreas.

33:18.178 --> 33:19.378
Yeah, you take her every time?

33:21.248 --> 33:22.515
You're a good man.

33:23.984 --> 33:25.951
I don't like her taking the bus.

33:25.986 --> 33:28.421
Strangers. You never know.

33:29.689 --> 33:31.957
True.

33:31.992 --> 33:34.260
What's your wife's name?

33:34.294 --> 33:36.562
Janine.

33:36.597 --> 33:38.197
Then I'm sorry, Janine.

33:40.133 --> 33:42.567
(Tires screeching)

33:54.280 --> 33:57.982
( ♪ )

33:58.017 --> 33:59.951
Elena: Those dead Mutts...

33:59.985 --> 34:02.187
how could Malcolm kill them all?

34:02.221 --> 34:04.822
This was on the neck of the
people who attacked us.

34:07.660 --> 34:09.226
None of this makes any sense.

34:12.097 --> 34:14.431
(Phone buzzing)

34:14.466 --> 34:15.632
Malcolm's in Baton Rouge.

34:15.668 --> 34:17.034
Do you know where he'll be?

34:17.069 --> 34:18.735
Clayton: (On phone) <i>I have an idea.</i>

34:18.771 --> 34:20.690
A spider hole he used to
hide in when he was hurt.

34:20.706 --> 34:22.005
I'll text you the coordinates.

34:22.041 --> 34:23.741
Nick: (On phone) <i>There's something else.</i>

34:25.110 --> 34:27.344
Jeremy didn't give you the full picture.

34:27.379 --> 34:29.079
The Alphas are threatening
to force him out

34:29.112 --> 34:32.349
<i>if we don't find Malcolm.</i>
Then we find him.

34:35.018 --> 34:36.753
Jeremy and Nick are flying to Louisiana.

34:36.788 --> 34:38.088
They got a lead on Malcolm.

34:38.121 --> 34:39.356
Let's ditch your car,

34:39.391 --> 34:40.591
and we'll drive down there and get him.

34:40.625 --> 34:41.757
They might have Rachel.

34:41.793 --> 34:44.873
( ♪ )

35:00.578 --> 35:02.011
(Effort grunt)

35:10.045 --> 35:13.581
(Vehicle approaching)

35:13.615 --> 35:16.821
( ♪ )

35:20.856 --> 35:22.123
He's here.

35:30.969 --> 35:33.009
Logan: All right, let's go.
What are we waiting for?

35:33.034 --> 35:35.135
Ah, ah, ah.

35:35.169 --> 35:37.571
We go in smart,

35:37.606 --> 35:39.740
we come out alive.

35:39.775 --> 35:41.141
And when we find her...

35:41.175 --> 35:43.877
I'll leave with her, take Mutt status.

35:45.546 --> 35:47.147
I'll raise my son as a Mutt,

35:47.181 --> 35:49.950
just like my father.

35:49.984 --> 35:53.887
Your son is part of my Pack.

35:53.922 --> 35:55.155
- You will bring him to me...
- Jeremy.

35:55.189 --> 35:56.689
And I will raise him.

35:56.724 --> 35:58.324
This is not a negotiation, Logan.

35:58.358 --> 35:59.893
This is the way it's going to be.

36:01.896 --> 36:03.830
All right.

36:03.864 --> 36:06.633
But don't kill Malcolm until
we know Rachel's safe.

36:06.667 --> 36:07.734
Please.

36:10.738 --> 36:12.104
I'm going to finish now

36:12.139 --> 36:15.474
what I should have
finished back at Stonehaven.

36:15.508 --> 36:17.977
What I should have finished years ago.

36:18.011 --> 36:21.888
( ♪ )

36:29.923 --> 36:31.022
(Banging)

36:33.860 --> 36:36.261
Jeremy: Malcolm?

36:36.295 --> 36:38.864
Malcolm: You think I haven't
been through worse this week?

36:41.334 --> 36:43.802
- You're nothing.
- Jeremy: No?

36:46.072 --> 36:48.906
I tracked you down.

36:48.941 --> 36:51.876
How does it feel to be
running scared, father?

36:51.910 --> 36:54.846
You're up for a conversation,
should I put on the kettle?

36:54.880 --> 36:57.048
Pete.

36:57.083 --> 36:59.050
Antonio.

36:59.085 --> 37:00.685
Philip.

37:00.719 --> 37:03.988
I'm holding you accountable
for all of their deaths.

37:04.022 --> 37:07.057
And I'll be accountable for yours.

37:07.092 --> 37:09.693
(Fighting grunts)

37:09.727 --> 37:12.867
( ♪ )

37:16.901 --> 37:18.368
Ahhh!

37:18.402 --> 37:20.169
You should have let me
teach you to fight.

37:20.204 --> 37:22.138
Then I wouldn't be able to surprise you.

37:22.172 --> 37:23.974
Woman's voice: Help!

37:30.680 --> 37:31.947
Woman's voice: Help!

37:35.952 --> 37:38.021
- Woman's voice: Help me!
- Rachel!

37:39.723 --> 37:41.124
She's out here.

37:41.158 --> 37:43.058
Logan!

37:43.092 --> 37:45.460
(Groan)
Ugh!

37:48.131 --> 37:50.499
(Mixed yells, grunts)

37:55.204 --> 37:57.773
Something's coming for us.
Protect yourself.

38:00.910 --> 38:02.110
Ugh!

38:04.380 --> 38:06.314
Rachel!

38:06.349 --> 38:08.950
Woman's voice: Logan! Help me!

38:12.021 --> 38:13.121
What is it?

38:15.357 --> 38:17.191
- She's not here, man.
- It was her!

38:17.225 --> 38:19.293
Well, she's not here.
You're hearing things.

38:21.196 --> 38:22.496
He can't kill Malcolm.

38:29.204 --> 38:30.337
(Fighting grunts)

38:30.372 --> 38:33.745
( ♪ )

38:38.780 --> 38:41.449
(Yells, grunts)

38:41.483 --> 38:44.923
( ♪ )

38:49.958 --> 38:51.058
Ugh!

38:53.427 --> 38:54.728
Jeremy!

38:56.430 --> 38:58.298
Aaah!

38:58.332 --> 38:59.833
(Scream)

38:59.867 --> 39:02.202
(Yelling in pain)

39:06.840 --> 39:08.040
Ahhh.

39:08.075 --> 39:09.175
(Attack yell)

39:12.179 --> 39:13.613
(Gagging, choking)

39:17.184 --> 39:18.418
Logan: Jeremy!

39:18.452 --> 39:19.785
She isn't here.

39:21.054 --> 39:22.454
(Panting)

39:26.827 --> 39:28.027
Where is Rachel?

39:30.097 --> 39:32.965
I suppose if you kill me
you'll never find out.

39:33.000 --> 39:36.273
( ♪ )

39:43.745 --> 39:47.181
(Nature din)
(Footsteps)

39:47.183 --> 39:49.817
Who are you looking for?
No one's coming to save you.

39:49.819 --> 39:51.920
Get me in the car and let's go.

39:51.922 --> 39:53.654
We can't stay anywhere too long.
It's not safe.

39:53.656 --> 39:55.390
What, you think you're safe with us?

39:55.392 --> 39:58.092
I would kill you now if I could.
>> And I would choose that over

39:58.094 --> 40:01.328
the other things I've seen this week.

40:01.330 --> 40:04.334
(Door creaks)
(Footsteps)

40:07.867 --> 40:10.357
We'll work Malcolm over.

40:10.386 --> 40:13.513
If he knows where she is we may get that.

40:14.054 --> 40:16.121
Or we may get lies...

40:18.083 --> 40:20.627
or we may get nothing.

40:25.048 --> 40:27.584
Something came at me in Rochester.

40:29.083 --> 40:31.112
(Sighs)

40:32.491 --> 40:34.592
Is that what this is about?

40:34.615 --> 40:37.584
Malcolm: It was branded
on their necks that symbol.

40:37.665 --> 40:41.585
It was also on the necks of the people
who jumped us at the shipping yards.

40:43.579 --> 40:47.553
(Phone clicks)
Were they responsible for this too?

40:50.625 --> 40:53.103
I've scratched the surface of
what that means, Clay,

40:53.105 --> 40:55.161
and nothing good could come from it.

40:55.186 --> 40:59.032
You need to keep me alive
for what's coming.

40:59.884 --> 41:01.035
(Grunts)

41:04.407 --> 41:05.625
(Car door slams)

41:10.858 --> 41:13.196
I found this inside.

41:15.142 --> 41:17.393
- It's the same symbol.
- Yeah.

41:18.798 --> 41:21.362
I'm going to stay on. Look into it.

41:21.364 --> 41:23.430
A professor I know in Tulane
specializing in Pagan symbology.

41:23.432 --> 41:25.732
Yeah, but what if it's nothing?

41:25.734 --> 41:27.785
What if he's just messing with us?

41:27.815 --> 41:30.582
No... I saw something in Malcolm's eyes

41:30.595 --> 41:33.830
I've never seen before. Fear.

41:37.783 --> 41:42.215
- Do you want me to stay?
- No, I want you to be there

41:42.217 --> 41:45.852
when Jeremy kills him.
And before that, you don't let

41:45.854 --> 41:47.621
him get in your head.

41:49.021 --> 41:52.079
He can't get in my head if
he's separated from his.

41:52.101 --> 41:55.040
What now? We can't distract them all.

41:55.571 --> 41:58.531
Wherever they're taking
Malcolm Danvers...

41:58.533 --> 42:00.718
is where we are going.

42:03.328 --> 42:07.173
(Door creaks)
(Footsteps)

42:15.134 --> 42:16.148
(Door closes)

42:16.150 --> 42:19.218
(Footsteps)

42:19.220 --> 42:23.092
♪

42:27.094 --> 42:30.933
♪

42:42.278 --> 42:44.294
- Did you find the wolf?
- We did.

42:44.295 --> 42:46.255
We'll save you soon.

42:46.294 --> 42:48.294
Alastair came back angry.

42:48.652 --> 42:51.004
Did he do anything to you?

42:51.411 --> 42:55.105
No, it was about the wolf, not me.

42:57.430 --> 43:00.249
Savannah, listen, he
isn't what he seems.

43:00.250 --> 43:02.102
Wait, can you hear that?

43:04.770 --> 43:08.379
I don't hear anything.
What is it, Savannah?

43:08.917 --> 43:10.685
The screams.

43:16.468 --> 43:17.987
(Grunts)

43:18.192 --> 43:20.880
(Pants)

43:31.280 --> 43:34.873
(Gasps)
(Screams)

